{
  "texts": [
    "Sentiment analysis has a lot of real-world applications, such as market research, customer service, political analysis, and brand management.",
    "In the last few years, researchers invested a lot of effort in developing automated techniques for sentiment analysis, including the valence aware dictionary and sentiment reasoner (VADER) method and text classification methods.",
    "The VADER method combines lexicon and rule-based approaches to analyze sentiment [2].",
    "It was that firstly developed by researchers at the University of Georgia.",
    "VADER uses a prebuilt dictionary of sentiment words that are scored on a scale from -4 for most negative to +4 for most positive."
  ]
}